          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 50Cr(g,n)49Cr cross section has been measured",
                " over the energy range Eg = 20.43 to Eg = 22.22 MeV",
                " using monochromatic g-rays from the 3H(p,g)4He",
                " reaction and detecting the resulting 49Cr positron",
                " activity. The g-rays were monitored by 12.7 cm x",
                " 15.2 cm NaI(Tl) crystal. The positron activity was",
                " was determined by a coincidence detector consisting",
                " of two 7.62 cm x 7.62 cm NaI(Tl) crystal set on the",
                " annihilation radiation photopeaks. The g-ray energy",
                " resolution was less than 110 keV over the whole",
                " energy range. structure in the cross section was",
                " not observed."
              ]
            }
          ],
